K8s comprises of several components:
- API Server: This acts as the frontend service for k8s as it is what interacts with the client.
- etcd: key-value store. Stores info of all nodes. Responsible for logging.
- Scheduler: Distributes work or containers amongst nodes.
- kubelet: Agent that runs on each node in a cluster
- controller: brain behind the operations.
- Container runtime: underlying software used to run containers e.g docker